<item>
            <title>[OAK-1422] Large number of queued EventGenerator.Continuation on big transactions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1422</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The queue of &lt;tt&gt;EventGenerator.Continuation&lt;/tt&gt; grows in the order of changed number of leave nodes instead of in the order of the depth of the changed sub tree. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is caused by the &lt;tt&gt;EventGenerator&lt;/tt&gt; processing events in a breath first manner causing events from each level of the tree to be held in the tree until all lower levels have been processed. I suggest to change the processing order to depth first, which should significantly lower the upper bound of the number of queued &lt;tt&gt;Continuation&lt;/tt&gt; instances. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
